# Akademiata WordPress theme

- **Repo:** https://github.com/irynaBilousSPDev/deAtaCennik.git (`origin`)
- **Optional remote:** `ata2026` → https://github.com/arinabilous/ata2026.git (only when user asks)
- **Text domain:** `akademiata` for all `__()`, `_e()`, `_x()`, `esc_html_e()`
- **Stack:** WordPress, ACF, WPML, Gulp (SCSS), Webpack (JS), Bootstrap 4 CDN (not npm BS5 on front)

## `functions.php` load order

`cpt-taxonomy.php` → `utilities.php` → `offer-pricing.php` → `ajax_filters.php` → `configure.php` → `youtube-api.php` → `offer-daily-interest.php` → `offer-start-timer.php` → `site-daily-visitors.php` → `js-css.php` → `shortcodes.php` → `breadcrumbs-functions.php` → `duplicate-cpt-posts.php` → `acf.php` → `load-cpt-slider.php` → `class-wp-mega-menu-walker.php` → `generate_keys_bch_mst.php` → `admin.php` (admin only). `wpml-string.php` is commented out.

## Build

```bash
npm install && npm run build   # or npm run dev
```

Edit `assets/src/` → outputs `assets/dist/css/main.css` and `assets/dist/js/{main,ajaxFilter,ajaxSlider,vendors}.js`. Rebuild after SCSS/JS changes.

## Comments (PHP, JS, SCSS, config)

- **Short and clear** — label sections or non-obvious business logic only.
- **Do not** state the obvious (e.g. “separate login (not dev)”, “this is production”, restating the variable name).
- **Config/env:** section labels only when useful (`# dev`, `# prod`); no prose tutorials in files.
- **Do not** bulk-rewrite existing comments unless the user asks; apply this to **new or touched** code.

## PHP conventions

- New helpers: prefer `akademiata_*` prefix; legacy `ata_*` for smart keys / news URLs.
- Match existing style in the file you edit (tabs vs spaces, `get_template_part` vs `locate_template`).
- **Windows:** never use PowerShell `Set-Content -Encoding UTF8` on theme PHP (breaks Polish characters).

## Cross-cutting behavior

- **Registration CTA:** show when `register_url` ACF is non-empty (`!empty($register_url)`).
- **Bachelor/master terms cache:** `akademiata_get_offer_terms()` in `utilities.php` — for performance on offer singles/cards, not for PG/MBA detail blocks (use `get_the_terms()` there).
- **logical_sync_key:** auto-generated on bachelor/master save (`configure/generate_keys_bch_mst.php`); powers Google calculator on single offers.
- **Offer start timer:** `configure/offer-start-timer.php` — Theme Settings → **Timer startu studiów** (enable, countdown target, show from/until, 4 phrase pairs). WPML String Translation context `akademiata-offer-start-timer`; EN/UK/RU fallbacks in `akademiata_get_theme_lang_string()`.

## External data

- Prices JSON: Google Apps Script (`configure/js-css.php` → `googleApiUrl`), docs in `apps-script/README.md`, fallback `prices.json`.
- YouTube: `configure/youtube-api.php` (Theme Settings → YouTube API, encrypted key) + REST `/wp-json/akademiata/v1/youtube` + `__YouTubeSlider.js`. Legacy `youtube-proxy.php` delegates to same handler. Optional `YOUTUBE_API_KEY` in `wp-config.php`.
- **Offer daily interest:** `configure/offer-daily-interest.php` — Theme Settings → **Licznik zainteresowania** (enable/disable, optional `active_from` date, default on). Singles bachelor/master with `register_url`. Daily reset at midnight; one-time prod launch date in code until first live day.
- **Site daily visitors:** `configure/site-daily-visitors.php` — same global toggle as offer interest counter; unique visitors across whole site per day (min 2 on prod). **REST + JS** (`siteDailyVisitors.js`) so WP Rocket page cache stays valid; filters `rocket_cache_reject_uri` + `rocket_delay_js_exclusions`. (Homepage **Decyzja na dziś** display removed from `front-page.php` for now.)

## Cursor rules

- Architecture docs: `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — update when code changes (`akademiata-maintain-rules.mdc`).
- Full audit: run **`/sync-rules`** after large refactors.
- Git: **`dev`** = daily work. **`main`** = production. **GitHub = source of truth** between PCs. **`/sync-git`** / **`npm run sync:git`** = pull `dev` + `main` (no SFTP). **`/deploy-dev`** = commit → **push `dev`** → SFTP (git-changed files only). Deploy blocks if uncommitted or unpushed. **`/push-dev`** = push only. **`/deploy-prod`** = merge `dev` → `main`, push both, SFTP prod. **`DEPLOY_FULL=true`** = rare full server sync.
- **GTM / gtag:** `akademiata_is_production()` — prod hosts only. **Cookiebot:** WP plugin only.
- **New CPT:** `akademiata_register_post_type()` — auto `author` + `revisions` + native admin boxes.
